ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
TOWER POWER: Building a tunnel beneath the Strait of Gibraltar (D5) is not 
Charles E. Kaempen's first dream. . . . In 1975, he suggested building a hollow 
plastic tower, 6,500 feet high and 325 feet wide. The idea: to disperse urban 
pollution in the upper atmosphere while producing water and generating 
electricity. Some experts said the concept was worth exploring, but it never 
got off the drawing board. Kristina Lindgren and David Reyes 
